    Building Microservices in springboot
In the past, what gets deployed is one entity and it scales as a single entity.
On the code side, you can have multiple modularity or projects but still have a monolith deployed.
But with micro services, what gets deployed is very different
    Todo
-Creating a few microservices.
-Having them communicate with each other.
-Monolith broken to micro services
-Difference between web service and micro service
    What is a Technology
A technology is used to solves a problem.
Technology we will use - Spring Cloud
Spring Cloud: This is one of the robust ways to create micro services.
    Prerequisites
-Java
-Spring Boot
    Movie Catalog API application
web service and micro service

step 1 - Create the 3 services
i.e create 3 projects from start.spring.io
dependencies
-Spring Web
    The three projects(services)
spring-catalog-service
movie-info-service
rating-data-service

@RequestMapping("/{userId}")
The data inside the {} tells springboot that it accepts a variable and it works together with @Pathvariable.

configure the port for each of the microservices/projects in the application.properties
-Good practice: always leave port 8080 free

    We have the 3 services/projects set up
The first connection which is calling the movie info api from the catalog service.
    How to make a REST call from your code
RestTemplate: We use it to make rest api calls.
web client: This is th harder way to make api calls.

